882","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-23/s7/b"},"text":"section 7(b) of the Act of Sept. 23, 1950","children":[],"tail":", except the 255th through 316th words, are omitted as executed. The 255th through 296th words are scheduled for repeal as superseded (see Table II–b), and the 297th through 316th words are codified in section 5501. The "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1876-08-15/ch287/s5"},"text":"Act of Aug. 15, 1876, ch. 287, § 5","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/19/169"},"text":"19 Stat. 169","children":[],"tail":", cited as authority for former section 46 was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1950-09-23/s7/a"},"text":"section 7(a) of the Act of Sept. 23, 1950","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In the last sentence, the word “removed” is substituted for “summarily removed” because of the provisions of the Lloyd-LaFollette Act, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/37/555"},"text":"37 Stat. 555","children":[],"tail":", as amended, and the Veterans’ Preference Act of 1944, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/387"},"text":"58 Stat. 387","children":[],"tail":", as amended, which are carried into this title."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Standard changes are made to conform with the definitions applicable and the style of this title as outlined in the preface to the report.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
